<html><head><title>Mutated Seabass Poker League</title><style type="text/css"><!----></style><link href="mspl.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"></head><body><div align="center"><p><img src="images/logo.gif"></p><p><img src="images/map.gif" border="0" usemap="#main_menu"><map name="main_menu"><area shape="rect" coords="506,15,570,41" href="http://mspl.bigwolfelittlewolfe.com"><area shape="rect" coords="409,15,473,41" href="players/players.htm"><area shape="rect" coords="309,15,373,41" href="leaders/leaders.htm"><area shape="rect" coords="218,15,269,41" href="rules/rules.htm"><area shape="rect" coords="112,14,181,38" href="events/2007schedule.htm"><area shape="rect" coords="24,14,73,40" href="index.htm"></map></p></div><h5>Recent News </h5><table width="500" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td><strong>12/17/06</strong></td><td>2006 season complete. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>12/17/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/061216.htm">December 16th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>12/3/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/061202.htm">December 2nd </a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>11/5/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/061104.htm">November 4th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>10/8/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/061007.htm">October 7th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>9/10/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/060909.htm">September 9th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>8/5/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/060804.htm">August 4th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>7/8/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/060707.htm">July 7th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>6/3/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/060602.htm">June 2nd</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>5/7/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/060506.htm">May 6th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>4/9/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/060408.htm">April 8th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>3/12/06</strong></td><td>2006 schedule changed for balance purposes.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>3/12/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/060311.htm">March 11th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>2/12/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/060211.htm">February 11th</a> tournament added. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>2/12/06</strong></td><td>2006 schedule changed to reflect results from Omaha vote. <strong></strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>    </strong><strong>1/15/06</strong></td><td>Results from <a href="events/060114.htm">January 14th</a> tournament added.</td></tr><tr><td>      <strong>12/23/05</strong></td><td>MSPL site URL, <a href="http://mspl.felarca.com">http://mspl.felarca.com</a>, created. </td></tr><tr><td><strong>12/22/05</strong></td><td>New look and feel added for MSPL site.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>12/18/05</strong></td><td>Added results from 12/17/05 practice tournament.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>12/11/05</strong></td><td> Announced launch of MSPL site.</td></tr></table><blockquote><hr size="1" color="#990000"><h5>Tournaments </h5><p>Starting time is 9:00pm. Tournaments will start as close to on-time as possible. Once a tournament begins, no player will be able to buy-in. If any player is going to be late, their best option is to call ahead to make sure they are included.</p><p>Tournament type will rotate on a monthly basis. January, April, May, July, August, October, andDecember tournaments will be Texas Hold&rsquo;em. February and August tournaments will be Omaha.March, June, and September tournaments will be 7-Card Stud.</p><hr size="1" color="#990000"><h5>Buy-in </h5><p>Buy-in for regular tournament in January through November is $15+$1. December&rsquo;s &ldquo;main event&rdquo; buy-inis$49+$1.</p><p>$10 per person involved in a regular tournament ($40 for the main event) is taken from the buy-inand placed in the tournament prize fund. 20% (rounded-up) of the field to a maximum of 8 positionsget paid out from the tournament prize fund. Click the appropriate link for a table with payouts for <a href="etc/payouts10.pdf" target="_blank">regulartournaments</a> and the <a href="etc/payouts40.pdf" target="_blank">main event</a>.</p><p>$2 per person ($5 for the main event) involved in a tournament is taken from the buy-in and placedin the Individual Bounty prize fund. For the main event, there is an additional $1 per person thatis set aside for one additional bounty. </p><p>$2.50 per person involved in a tournament is taken from the buy-in and placed in the Points Leader prize fund.</p><p>$0.50 per person involved in a tournament is taken from the buy-in and placed in the Bounty Hunter prize fund.</p><p>$1 per person involved in a tournament is taken as a cover charge to pay for the cost of tables, chairs, etc. </p><hr size="1" color="#990000"><h5>Points </h5><p>There are three types of points that can be earned throughout the season: Base, Bonus, and KO.</p><p>Base points are awarded based upon finish within a tournament. The formula for Place points is &ldquo;N &ndash; P + 1&rdquo; whereN is the total number of people in the tournament and P is the position a given player finishedin. A table for base points can be found <a href="etc/poker_base_points.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>. </p><p>Bonus points are awarded based upon finish within a tournament. All players that finish withinthe top 20% (rounded-up) of the field are awarded bonus points using the formula &ldquo;Base / P&rdquo; whereBase is the number of base points a given player earned and P is the position a given player hasfinished in. A table for bonus points can be found <a href="etc/poker_bonus_points.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>.</p><p>For the main event, base point and bonus points are doubled.</p><p>KO points are awarded based on the number of players a player has eliminated.</p><hr size="1" color="#990000"><h5>Points Leader </h5><p>Players will be ranked by the total qualifying points they have received throughout the season. Qualifying points will be:</p><ul><li>The Top 8 Base points received from January to November</li><li>Base points received from the main event in December</li><li>All Bonus points received during the season</li><li>All KO points received during the season</li></ul><p>The highest ranked player at the end of the season will receive 75% or $500 (whichever is less) of the Points Leader prize fund. The leftover amount will be reserved for a special tournament held between the top 8 Point Leaders. </p><hr size="1" color="#990000"><h5>KO Leader </h5><p>Whoever has the most KO points at the end of the season will receive 75% or $125 (whichever is less) of the KO Leader prize fund.The leftover amount will be reserved for a  Individual Bounty placed on one individual during the special tournament held between the top 8 Point Leaders. <br><br><hr size="1" color="#990000"><img src="images/bounty_chip.gif" width="123" height="122" align="left"></p><h5>Individual Bounties</h5><p>One person randomly selected per starting table in the tournament. Each of those players will have a bounty placed on them equal to the total amount of the Individual Bounty prize fund divided by the number of players with bounties placed on them. Whomever KOs from the tournament any player with a bounty on them will receive the Individual Bounty prize fund. A table with individual bounties information can be found <a href="etc/individual_bounties.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>. </p><br><br clear="all"><hr size="1" color="#990000"></p><h5>Schedules/Time</h5><p>For Texas Hold'em and Omaha, a small and big blind will be used. At the end of a round, the blinds will raise according to the blind schedule. Blinds are raised on the first deal in the new round.  A table with the blind schedule can be found <a href="etc/blind_schedule.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>.</p><p>For 7-Card Stud, antes will be collected at the beginning of each hand from all players at the table. The amount of the ante will also serve as the minimum bet. At the end of a round, the antes will raise according to the ante schedule. Antes are raised on the first deal in the new round. A table with the ante schedule can be found <a href="etc/ante_schedule.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>.</p><p>All rounds are 15 minutes long unless otherwise noted. The timer will run continuously. The timer will only stop when tables are being consolidated, chips are being colored-up, or at the discretion of league management.</p><p>If requested by another player at the table, a player can have a timer placed on them. This means that the player will have 30 seconds to act before their hand will be declared dead. The player will be reminded they are being timed when they have 10 seconds left to act.</p><hr size="1" color="#990000"><h5>Buttons </h5><p>In Texas Hold'em and Omaha, a dealer button, small blind, and big blind is used. Once the dealer button is placed, the small blind is placed to the left of the dealer button and the big blind is to the left of the small blind. At the end of a hand, the dealer button moves to the next available player to the left of the current placement and are followed by the small and big blinds accordingly.</p><p>In 7-Card Stud, only a dealer button is used. </p></blockquote></body></html>